@Nobody 3 I've reached the point with Thursday puzzles that I begin by putting up a virtual white flag, admitting surrender to the constructor. I don't have a beef with the creators of the Thursday puzzles - more power to them. I just know I will never solve one in its entirety. The REBUS puzzles are incredibly frustrating because one never knows what square is a REBUS square; there is no warning that you are about to land on a REBUS square.

